"rationale": "The original SOP-103 addressed only audit trail generation, immutability, review, and retention. The new FDA regulation update mandates additional system-enforced controls to ensure overall data integrity and trustworthiness. The revised SOP incorporates: (1) password complexity, aging, and account lockout after 3 failed attempts (21 CFR Part 11.300(a)-(b)); (2) session timeout after 15 minutes of inactivity (21 CFR Part 11.300(c)); (3) encryption of transmitted records using TLS 1.3 (21 CFR Part 11.30); (4) enhanced audit trail requirements including cryptographic sign-off of reviews and a 30-day review cycle (FDA-2026-N-8841 Sections 3.1-3.2); (5) dual-authorization for SOP modifications and document releases (21 CFR Part 11.10(a) and FDA-2026-N-8841 Section 6.5); and (6) incident reporting within 4 hours (FDA-2026-N-8841 Section 4.2). These changes ensure the SOP fully aligns with the regulation's goal of making electronic records equivalent to paper records with robust security and traceability."
